07:46.590 --> 07:48.173 align:middle line:84%
is, gosh, I wish I
had done it sooner.

07:48.173 --> 07:55.380 align:middle line:90%


07:55.380 --> 07:58.515 align:middle line:84%
When we started our venture
capital firm, Seven Seven Six,

07:58.515 --> 08:01.330 align:middle line:84%
we knew we wanted to do
everything differently.

08:01.330 --> 08:02.910 align:middle line:84%
And that all
started with hiring.

08:02.910 --> 08:06.180 align:middle line:84%
We did something that's
actually atypical in venture,

08:06.180 --> 08:08.430 align:middle line:90%
which is open applications.

08:08.430 --> 08:11.910 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't seem very special
until you realize that VC

08:11.910 --> 08:14.040 align:middle line:90%
is a very insular industry.

08:14.040 --> 08:16.020 align:middle line:84%
And the vast majority
of people all

08:16.020 --> 08:18.430 align:middle line:84%
come from within
the same networks.

08:18.430 --> 08:22.740 align:middle line:84%
In fact, one study showed
that 40% of all VCs

08:22.740 --> 08:26.460 align:middle line:84%
graduated from
Stanford or Harvard.

08:26.460 --> 08:29.880 align:middle line:84%
As someone who wasn't in
that group, but certainly

08:29.880 --> 08:34.049 align:middle line:84%
feels a responsibility to
get the very best working

08:34.049 --> 08:36.820 align:middle line:84%
at our firm, we tried
a different approach.

08:36.820 --> 08:38.250 align:middle line:90%
We announced it on Twitter.

08:38.250 --> 08:41.429 align:middle line:84%
And we developed applications
that were holistic,

08:41.429 --> 08:43.710 align:middle line:90%
didn't ask people for their CV--

08:43.710 --> 08:44.710 align:middle line:90%
because let's face it.

08:44.710 --> 08:47.130 align:middle line:84%
We don't ask founders
for their resumes.

08:47.130 --> 08:49.440 align:middle line:84%
Why should we ask
members of our own team?

08:49.440 --> 08:50.520 align:middle line:90%
We asked for essays.

08:50.520 --> 08:54.450 align:middle line:84%
We asked for explanations of
not just experiences, but also

08:54.450 --> 08:55.270 align:middle line:90%
potential.

08:55.270 --> 08:58.320 align:middle line:84%
And we were able to get
over 1,200 applicants, which

08:58.320 --> 09:01.440 align:middle line:84%
for a brand new
firm isn't too bad.

09:01.440 --> 09:05.348 align:middle line:84%
We got some pretty
interesting results.

09:05.348 --> 09:07.390 align:middle line:84%
You see this kind of
creativity that doesn't just

09:07.390 --> 09:09.070 align:middle line:84%
show up on a resume,
because you're

09:09.070 --> 09:13.660 align:middle line:84%
asking questions that don't stop
with the sort of bare minimum,

09:13.660 --> 09:16.240 align:middle line:84%
but actually push applicants
to go a little further to talk

09:16.240 --> 09:18.790 align:middle line:84%
about the why in their own
lives and their own stories.

09:18.790 --> 09:56.590 align:middle line:90%


09:56.590 --> 09:59.860 align:middle line:84%
ALEXIS OHANIAN: This is exactly
what we could have hoped for,

09:59.860 --> 10:02.470 align:middle line:84%
but nothing we could
have predicted.

10:02.470 --> 10:06.040 align:middle line:84%
Of those 1,200
applicants, over 82%

10:06.040 --> 10:10.170 align:middle line:84%
