underrepresented in tech.

10:10.170 --> 10:14.340 align:middle line:84%
And I think this really
speaks to the power of hiring

10:14.340 --> 10:17.850 align:middle line:84%
for a broader purpose,
and being willing to break

10:17.850 --> 10:23.610 align:middle line:84%
from the common examples of
expertise or credentials,

10:23.610 --> 10:26.970 align:middle line:84%
and actually getting
to talent that

10:26.970 --> 10:29.580 align:middle line:84%
is going to have an approach
that's unorthodox, that's

10:29.580 --> 10:32.100 align:middle line:84%
unconventional, but
exactly what you

10:32.100 --> 10:34.910 align:middle line:90%
need in a business like this.

